headline.main: LATEST INTELLIGENCE; By Telegraph to the New-York Daily Times. FROM WASHINGTON. THE PRESIDENT'S MESSAGE. OUR RELATIONS WITH GREAT BRITAIM. REPORT OF THE SECRETARY OF THE NAVY. The Action of the Naval Retiting Board Sustained. REPORT OF THE POSTMASTER-GENERAL.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Message took everybody by surprise. Notody expected it, as no former President ever considered it proper to address a message to Congress until after it was organized.
